    "body": "Edit: marking this as a good first issue. It's really straightforward. Just find every location where `eslint-plugin-ban` is added as a dependency and remove it using `yarn remove eslint-plugin-ban`. You'll also want to remove it at the root level with `yarn remove eslint-plugin-ban -W`. I *think* this won't break anything, but let's just make a PR that removes the dependency and see if anything breaks.",
